WEBVTT

1
00:00:17.115 --> 00:00:23.087
(♪ "1812 OVERTURE")

2
00:02:41.059 --> 00:02:42.760
WOMAN: Oh! Oh!

3
00:02:42.762 --> 00:02:43.828
MAN: What?

4
00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:45.830
The song.
The song?

5
00:02:45.832 --> 00:02:49.033
The... the song...
uh. the "1812 overture."

6
00:02:49.035 --> 00:02:51.936
The... the finale
from "1812 overture."

7
00:02:51.938 --> 00:02:54.672
Yeah.
What about it?

8
00:02:54.674 --> 00:02:57.842
Well. you just... it was
building to the big finale.

9
00:02:57.844 --> 00:03:00.344
And you cut it off right before it ended.
Oh. god. I'm sorry.

10
00:03:00.346 --> 00:03:02.980
Oh. no. Please don't be sorry.
No. I'm just being stupid.

11
00:03:02.982 --> 00:03:05.383
It's... it's just that
whenever a song comes on.

12
00:03:05.385 --> 00:03:07.952
If it... if it's building to. like.
the big chorus or whatever.

13
00:03:07.954 --> 00:03:11.756
And if it gets cut off. then I
feel unfulfilled psychologically.

14
00:03:12.924 --> 00:03:15.092
Oh. Huh.

15
00:03:15.094 --> 00:03:16.961
You don't get that?

16
00:03:16.963 --> 00:03:18.963
Uh.

17
00:03:18.965 --> 00:03:20.798
I guess I haven't really thought about it.

18
00:03:20.800 --> 00:03:22.299
You didn't want to hear how it ended?

19
00:03:22.301 --> 00:03:24.235
I've heard it before.
No. I'm sure you have.

20
00:03:24.237 --> 00:03:26.871
You didn't want to hear it just now?

21
00:03:26.873 --> 00:03:30.007
No... I mean. yeah. Sure. You
want me to put it back on?

22
00:03:30.009 --> 00:03:32.943
Oh. no. no. Please. no. Then we'd be
sitting in a car listening to a song...

23
00:03:32.945 --> 00:03:35.413
Guess what? I want to hear it now.
(CHUCKLES)

24
00:03:35.415 --> 00:03:37.848
MAN ON RADIO: Maybe during our
previous membership campaign.

25
00:03:37.850 --> 00:03:40.317
You stood on the sidelines and
said "I'll wait to call in"...

26
00:03:40.319 --> 00:03:42.386
Right. We were listening
to the radio.

27
00:03:42.388 --> 00:03:44.689
The radio.
Yeah. it's the radio.

28
00:03:44.691 --> 00:03:46.323
MAN ON RADIO: <i>Wait no more.</i>

29
00:03:46.325 --> 00:03:48.325
<i>There's a pledge drive
right now.</i>

30
00:03:48.327 --> 00:03:50.294
We can go inside now.
Oh. okay. Yeah.

31
00:03:56.001 --> 00:03:57.835
(HORN HONKS) Oh. could you...

32
00:03:57.837 --> 00:03:59.336
Oh. sorry. Uh...
(HORN HONKS)

33
00:04:01.206 --> 00:04:02.773
(CHIRPS) Sorry. You
have to... all right.

34
00:04:02.775 --> 00:04:04.041
Yeah.
(HONKS. CHIRPS)

35
00:04:04.043 --> 00:04:07.211
That should do it.
Ahh! Right.

36
00:04:07.213 --> 00:04:10.114
Can I. uh. help you with it?
No. no. I got it.

37
00:04:10.116 --> 00:04:11.949
(HONKS) Hope you like it.

38
00:04:11.951 --> 00:04:13.884
Have you made it for brunch before?

39
00:04:13.886 --> 00:04:17.488
Not vegan. No. Lexi's gone vegan.
so everyone has to suffer.

40
00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:20.925
And... and Lexi is. uh. Peter's wife?
Lexi is Buck's wife.

41
00:04:20.927 --> 00:04:22.426
Emma is Pete's wife.

42
00:04:22.428 --> 00:04:23.828
Okay. Yes.

43
00:04:23.830 --> 00:04:27.231
All right.
(DOG BARKING)

44
00:04:27.233 --> 00:04:29.900
If Lexi and Buck start singing songs.

45
00:04:29.902 --> 00:04:33.037
Just nod and smile and pretend it's good.
Okay. (CHUCKLES)

46
00:04:33.039 --> 00:04:36.507
One more thing. Don't say anything
about shane and Hedy’s wedding.

47
00:04:36.509 --> 00:04:38.442
Who?
Shane and Hedy.

48
00:04:38.444 --> 00:04:39.877
Shane and Hedy... no wedding.
Long story.

49
00:04:39.879 --> 00:04:40.878
Okay.

50
00:04:41.413 --> 00:04:43.347
Ohh!

51
00:04:43.349 --> 00:04:45.116
(♪ POP) Hi.

52
00:04:45.118 --> 00:04:47.151
Okay. Hi. hon.

53
00:04:47.153 --> 00:04:49.353
Hi.
So this is him?

54
00:04:49.355 --> 00:04:51.055
Glenn.
I'm Emma.

55
00:04:51.057 --> 00:04:53.190
Hi.
Ooh. Good choice.

56
00:04:53.192 --> 00:04:55.292
Great. Come in. kids.
Please.

57
00:04:56.495 --> 00:05:00.030
Wow. This place is great.
Thank you.

58
00:05:00.032 --> 00:05:03.000
Do you. uh. rent or own?
We are proud homeowners.

59
00:05:03.002 --> 00:05:05.536
We got it really cheap because there
was a murder-suicide in the kitchen.

60
00:05:05.538 --> 00:05:07.438
Oh. really?
Yeah.

61
00:05:07.440 --> 00:05:10.007
Technically. the couple died in the
ambulance on the way to the hospital.

62
00:05:10.009 --> 00:05:12.877
But the real estate agent said
everybody else was spooked away.

63
00:05:12.879 --> 00:05:14.078
Wow.
Hello.

64
00:05:14.080 --> 00:05:16.814
Hi. Hi.
Hi. I'm Hedy.

65
00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:18.349
This is glenn.
Glenn.

66
00:05:18.351 --> 00:05:21.352
Glenn. Nice to meet you.
Nice to meet you.

67
00:05:21.354 --> 00:05:26.023
Can I. uh. take your coat? I'm putting
it upstairs on the bed in the bedroom...

68
00:05:26.025 --> 00:05:31.395
And we've also hired her as our coat-check girl.
Oh. congratulations.

69
00:05:31.397 --> 00:05:34.465
Yeah. Good. Please remember to tip her.
She gets real mad.

70
00:05:34.467 --> 00:05:36.333
(CHUCKLES) I'm serious.

71
00:05:36.335 --> 00:05:38.903
Do you want me to put that on the table?
I'll just put it in the kitchen.

72
00:05:38.905 --> 00:05:40.871
Jenny and gordon aren't here yet.

73
00:05:40.873 --> 00:05:44.909
We're not waiting for jenny and gordon to eat?
No. We'll give them till 12:30.

74
00:05:44.911 --> 00:05:49.380
'cause jenny and gordon are notoriously late.
Oh. I got friends like that.

75
00:05:49.382 --> 00:05:52.082
No. they're worse.
WOMAN: Tracy! Hey. hey. hey!

76
00:05:52.084 --> 00:05:55.820
Oh. it's so good to see you.

77
00:05:55.822 --> 00:05:58.022
Hey. how are you. Pete?
Pete. glenn.

78
00:05:58.024 --> 00:06:01.325
Yeah. Glenn. Welcome to our humble abode.
Oh. thanks. It's adorable.

79
00:06:01.327 --> 00:06:05.462
Oh! I've heard so much about you.
Oh. thanks.

80
00:06:05.464 --> 00:06:08.499
This is Lexi.
Oh. Oh. the vegan.

81
00:06:08.501 --> 00:06:11.302
The vegan? That's how she refers to me?
I'm the vegan?

82
00:06:11.304 --> 00:06:13.504
No. No. 'cause we were
talking about the stew.

83
00:06:13.506 --> 00:06:15.306
Oh.
She just mentioned... yeah.

84
00:06:15.308 --> 00:06:17.908
Right. Honey. I told you you didn't
have to make anything different.

85
00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:20.144
I'd be fine. I didn't want
you to feel left out.

86
00:06:20.146 --> 00:06:22.379
If I didn't want to be left out.
I wouldn't be a vegan. right?

87
00:06:22.381 --> 00:06:24.515
Well. I made it. and it's delicious.

88
00:06:24.517 --> 00:06:26.183
I'm not even hungry. so...
it's really good.

89
00:06:26.185 --> 00:06:28.018
You kids are so cute.
Oh.

90
00:06:28.020 --> 00:06:29.887
Oh. thanks for coming.
Do you want a drink?

91
00:06:29.889 --> 00:06:32.223
Uh. yes. please.

92
00:06:32.225 --> 00:06:34.058
(WHISPERING) Sorry about that.

93
00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:37.228
Bring your soup?
Uh. started a soup.

94
00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:40.898
Oh. yes. I've been there. Um.
babe. I put your coat on the bed.

95
00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:43.534
So whenever you're ready to put
the phone away. I got this.

96
00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:46.937
Um. you've got. like. five minutes.
No. I've 25 minutes.

97
00:06:46.939 --> 00:06:49.406
We've been here for 15. It
starts when we get here.

98
00:06:49.408 --> 00:06:51.508
No. it starts when we were talking about it.

99
00:06:51.510 --> 00:06:53.244
Babe. I'm in the middle of an auction.

100
00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:55.412
Can you just say hi to glenn?
Human interaction.

101
00:06:57.282 --> 00:07:01.118
Can I help you? No. I got it. Please. relax.
Do you want a mimosa?

102
00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:03.087
Okay. You sure that you don't need my help?
Yeah. I got it.

103
00:07:03.089 --> 00:07:05.422
Uh. glenn. a mimosa? Oh. no...

104
00:07:05.424 --> 00:07:08.959
I think glenn looks like a man that
appreciates the finer things in life.

105
00:07:08.961 --> 00:07:11.962
How about a scotch?
Uh. sure.

106
00:07:11.964 --> 00:07:14.265
All right. These snap
peas are the shit.

107
00:07:14.267 --> 00:07:17.968
He's cute.
Thanks.

108
00:07:17.970 --> 00:07:20.404
Can you behave please?
What? What did I do?

109
00:07:20.406 --> 00:07:23.274
Literally. we just walked in the door and
you're already picking a fight with me.

110
00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:25.576
How is that different from every
other time we see each other?

111
00:07:25.578 --> 00:07:28.579
I'm on a date. and I'm
trying to impress the man.

112
00:07:28.581 --> 00:07:31.181
What number date is this. tracy?
Third.

113
00:07:31.183 --> 00:07:36.053
Oh. wow. If we make it to
number five. we'll be golden.

114
00:07:36.055 --> 00:07:38.422
What is that supposed to mean?

115
00:07:38.424 --> 00:07:40.491
Just that usually you cut them off before that.
You check the scores?

116
00:07:40.493 --> 00:07:43.260
I don't know.
Are you online?

117
00:07:43.262 --> 00:07:45.629
I'm on eBay.
Why are you on eBay?

118
00:07:45.631 --> 00:07:47.398
He's trying to get a comic book.

119
00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:50.167
No. it's not just a comic book.
It's colorful.

120
00:07:50.169 --> 00:07:53.637
Um. it's a near-mint
X-Men. 120.

121
00:07:53.639 --> 00:07:55.973
The first appearance of Alpha Flight.

122
00:07:55.975 --> 00:07:58.042
I have no idea what you're talking about.
What is an Alpha Flight?

123
00:07:58.044 --> 00:08:00.311
It's a canadian superhero team
from Marvel comics.

124
00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:02.546
There's a canadian superhero team?
(CHUCKLES)

125
00:08:02.548 --> 00:08:05.115
Who do they fight...
Quebec secessionists?

126
00:08:05.117 --> 00:08:08.118
No. This guy has it on sale for five
dollars. and it's worth over 160.

127
00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:10.254
Whoa!
Wait. 160 U.S.?

128
00:08:10.256 --> 00:08:12.589
Wait. Where did you say that you
met glenn. at the hospital?

129
00:08:12.591 --> 00:08:15.125
At the grocery store.

130
00:08:15.127 --> 00:08:17.227
(♪ ALT ROCK)
<i>Where'd you and tracy meet?</i>

131
00:08:17.229 --> 00:08:21.298
Online. Well. no shame in that.
That's where we found our vet.

132
00:08:21.300 --> 00:08:22.666
(GLASSES CLINK)

133
00:08:27.739 --> 00:08:30.040
That's great.
That's really good.

134
00:08:30.042 --> 00:08:32.476
Yeah. it'll help you get through this.
(CHUCKLES)

135
00:08:32.478 --> 00:08:34.278
I'm sorry. What?

136
00:08:34.280 --> 00:08:37.147
Couples brunch. Oh. no. I'm
looking forward to it.

137
00:08:37.149 --> 00:08:39.550
Really?
Yeah.

138
00:08:41.319 --> 00:08:43.687
Can I ask you a question. glenn?
Sure.

139
00:08:43.689 --> 00:08:46.757
If you had to call someone up.
tell them some bad news.

140
00:08:46.759 --> 00:08:49.426
Would you tell them right away
or would you chitchat first?

141
00:08:51.229 --> 00:08:54.231
Chitchat. Yeah. You know. small talk.
"how you doin'?"

142
00:08:54.233 --> 00:08:55.766
No. I...
"what's goin' on?"

143
00:08:55.768 --> 00:08:57.768
I know. I know. "Nice weather.
Just... it's crazy."

144
00:08:57.770 --> 00:09:00.304
Right. right. No. um...

145
00:09:00.306 --> 00:09:05.242
Uh. well. I suppose it would depend
on the severity of the bad news.

146
00:09:05.244 --> 00:09:08.545
Hmm. What do you mean?
Uh. well.

147
00:09:08.547 --> 00:09:11.382
If I'm calling to let somebody
know that. um. you know.

148
00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:14.418
A family member passed away. then no chitchat.

149
00:09:14.420 --> 00:09:16.420
I wouldn't beat around the
bush with that. Right.

150
00:09:16.422 --> 00:09:20.524
Um. but if I was calling
to let them know that. uh.

151
00:09:20.526 --> 00:09:24.028
You know. they didn't get an
apartment. then. yeah. chitchat.

152
00:09:24.030 --> 00:09:25.429
Yeah. you know...
mmm.

153
00:09:25.431 --> 00:09:28.399
Talk a little bit. You in the
apartment rental business?

154
00:09:28.401 --> 00:09:31.335
No. No. I'm a teacher.

155
00:09:31.337 --> 00:09:35.372
So why do you call people and tell
them they didn't get an apartment?

156
00:09:36.508 --> 00:09:40.044
(CHUCKLES)
I... I don't.

157
00:09:40.046 --> 00:09:42.379
I'm sorry. I thought the
conversation was hypothetical.

158
00:09:42.381 --> 00:09:44.581
No. the conversation is real. glenn.

159
00:09:44.583 --> 00:09:47.251
The problem is hypothetical.

160
00:09:48.153 --> 00:09:50.287
Oh.
Yeah.

161
00:10:03.201 --> 00:10:05.602
Hey. Are we gonna talk about
this. or are you just gonna...

162
00:10:08.773 --> 00:10:11.241
You need something?
No. I'm okay.

163
00:10:11.243 --> 00:10:14.111
