Hmm.

164
00:10:14.113 --> 00:10:15.779
You getting a signal? Hmm?

165
00:10:15.781 --> 00:10:17.848
On your phone?
Mmm.

166
00:10:19.584 --> 00:10:22.086
Well. feel free to use my
computer in the living room.

167
00:10:22.088 --> 00:10:23.754
Oh. I don't want to
interrupt brunch. Mmm.

168
00:10:23.756 --> 00:10:26.090
I got nothing.
Very considerate.

169
00:10:26.092 --> 00:10:28.425
Um. well. the reception
back here is pretty spotty.

170
00:10:28.427 --> 00:10:30.427
You might want to try
the front porch. Okay.

171
00:10:30.429 --> 00:10:33.764
I can drink this out there? Yeah.
Of course you can. Why would you...

172
00:10:34.833 --> 00:10:36.667
Weird.

173
00:10:36.669 --> 00:10:39.103
Emma. we need to talk about this.

174
00:10:42.740 --> 00:10:46.510
So glenn agrees with me.
About what?

175
00:10:46.512 --> 00:10:49.446
That it's better to just
rip the band-aid off.

176
00:10:49.448 --> 00:10:51.849
What did you tell him? I
didn't tell him anything.

177
00:10:51.851 --> 00:10:54.251
I just asked him a hypothetical question.

178
00:10:54.253 --> 00:10:57.254
Well. he's not stupid. Pete. He's
gonna know what you're asking for.

179
00:10:57.256 --> 00:11:00.324
We just met the guy. How is he gonna
have any idea what I'm asking for?

180
00:11:00.326 --> 00:11:02.292
And how... how do we know
he's not stupid?

181
00:11:02.294 --> 00:11:03.727
(SIGHS) We had an agreement.

182
00:11:03.729 --> 00:11:05.562
Yeah. well. agreements change.

183
00:11:05.564 --> 00:11:08.198
No. they don't.
That's why they're agreements.

184
00:11:08.200 --> 00:11:10.868
This is awkward.
Well. deal with it.

185
00:11:10.870 --> 00:11:14.171
Yeah. I'll deal with it.

186
00:11:14.173 --> 00:11:17.174
(CHILDREN CHATTERING.
LAUGHING)

187
00:11:17.176 --> 00:11:20.644
(BEEPING) Damn. I bet
this game is so good too.

188
00:11:20.646 --> 00:11:23.213
I got nothing.
Me neither.

189
00:11:23.215 --> 00:11:27.184
I'm with at&t. How about you?
I have no idea.

190
00:11:27.186 --> 00:11:29.586
But I will ask this young lady to
use her phone. Mom. slow down.

191
00:11:29.588 --> 00:11:32.789
No. I'm not at home. No.
I'm not watching the news.

192
00:11:32.791 --> 00:11:34.858
Excuse me. miss?
Miss?

193
00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:37.227
Hey. can I. uh. borrow your phone real quick?

194
00:11:37.229 --> 00:11:38.896
I'm currently on the phone.
Oh. okay. I'll wait.

195
00:11:38.898 --> 00:11:40.631
What's his name?
Could you not...

196
00:11:40.633 --> 00:11:42.466
(SIREN WAILING)
What's his name?

197
00:11:42.468 --> 00:11:44.501
Mom? No. I didn't...
he's cute.

198
00:11:44.503 --> 00:11:45.736
