- An evening bag or a bag bag?

211
00:12:16.735 --> 00:12:19.503
A bag bag. Do you want to
come upstairs and see it?

212
00:12:19.505 --> 00:12:22.639
Yeah.
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

213
00:12:22.641 --> 00:12:24.875
I'll... I'll just be right back.
(SIRENS CONTINUES)

214
00:12:26.544 --> 00:12:28.812
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

215
00:12:33.218 --> 00:12:36.253
(♪ ROCK)

216
00:12:39.490 --> 00:12:41.491
Mmm! Good carrots.

217
00:12:43.895 --> 00:12:46.363
You want to see my glockenspiel?

218
00:12:48.233 --> 00:12:51.501
Oh. you're. uh. referring to
the musical instrument? Yes.

219
00:12:51.503 --> 00:12:53.837
(CHUCKLES)
What else would I be referring to?

220
00:12:53.839 --> 00:12:55.639
No. I don't...
uh. 'cause... yeah.

221
00:12:55.641 --> 00:13:00.377
Tracy had mentioned that. uh. you
and Buck. uh. perform. Oh. yeah.

222
00:13:00.379 --> 00:13:02.512
We perform all right.

223
00:13:02.514 --> 00:13:05.749
If you behave yourself at brunch
today. maybe we'll let you tap it.

224
00:13:05.751 --> 00:13:07.351
(CHUCKLES)

225
00:13:12.557 --> 00:13:14.491
Do you bump?
(TYPING)

226
00:13:14.493 --> 00:13:17.794
Hmm? Excuse me?
Bump. It's an App.

227
00:13:17.796 --> 00:13:21.398
Oh. yeah. Oh. the thing with
the... the information sharing.

228
