00:23:05.917 --> 00:23:07.217
Yes!
(TOGETHER) We know!

454
00:23:08.919 --> 00:23:12.255
Did I miss something? Pete and
Emma are getting a divorce.

455
00:23:12.257 --> 00:23:14.290
Really? Why?

456
00:23:14.292 --> 00:23:16.993
Okay. You know what?

457
00:23:16.995 --> 00:23:20.897
This is not how this was
supposed to go down. Yeah.

458
00:23:20.899 --> 00:23:23.299
We wanted to wait until the
end of brunch to tell you.

459
00:23:23.301 --> 00:23:28.071
But we've just decided that it's what's right.

460
00:23:28.073 --> 00:23:31.474
That's really vague.
EMMA: Well. it's complicated. Lexi.

461
00:23:31.476 --> 00:23:33.243
Marriage is complicated.
You know that.

462
00:23:33.245 --> 00:23:36.079
So it's a mutual thing.
PETE: Yeah.

463
00:23:36.081 --> 00:23:37.981
It's not like one of us caught the
other one cheating or anything.

464
00:23:37.983 --> 00:23:41.517
This isn't happening. No.
you're not getting a divorce.

465
00:23:41.519 --> 00:23:45.355
No. you'll still see us.
okay? Just not together.

466
00:23:45.357 --> 00:23:48.992
Well. you know. maybe physically
together. but not <i>together</i> together.

467
00:23:48.994 --> 00:23:51.594
But what we don't want is people picking sides.

468
00:23:51.596 --> 00:23:54.230
We really want to remain
close friends with all of you.

469
00:23:54.232 --> 00:23:57.433
Yeah. Unless some of you feel very
strongly about one of us over the other.

470
00:23:57.435 --> 00:23:59.602
Tracy. for instance.

471
00:23:59.604 --> 00:24:02.538
If you want to stay in touch with Emma
and completely shut me out of your life.

472
00:24:02.540 --> 00:24:05.275
- I'd understand.
- No. Pete. I would never.

473
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:08.678
Just. you know. think about it. You
don't need to make a decision now.

474
00:24:08.680 --> 00:24:11.481
So does this mean brunch is over?
Do you want us to leave?

475
00:24:13.017 --> 00:24:16.119
Shane. they just told us
they're getting a divorce.

476
00:24:16.121 --> 00:24:18.955
- And you're still thinking about Alpha Force?
- Alpha flight.

477
00:24:18.957 --> 00:24:20.657
I honestly didn't know
if they wanted us to leave.

478
00:24:20.659 --> 00:24:22.926
Because I have a feeling it's about
to get a little uncomfortable.

479
00:24:22.928 --> 00:24:24.627
Oh. do you have that feeling?

480
00:24:24.629 --> 00:24:28.364
Which is exactly why I wanted to wait
until after we ate to bring this up.

481
00:24:31.001 --> 00:24:33.102
(SIGHS) You know what?

482
00:24:33.104 --> 00:24:35.438
He's right. It is about
to get uncomfortable.

483
00:24:35.440 --> 00:24:36.940
But I'll be the one who's leaving.

484
00:24:40.477 --> 00:24:42.045
(MOUTHING WORDS. SIGHS)

485
00:24:42.047 --> 00:24:44.113
(SIGHS)

486
00:24:45.616 --> 00:24:48.551
(WATER GURGLING)

487
00:24:48.553 --> 00:24:51.654
Oh. hey. I think the power's out.
Shut the fuck up. glenn!

488
00:24:54.458 --> 00:24:56.659
I am so sorry.
I didn't mean that.

489
00:24:56.661 --> 00:25:00.630
I'm under a lot of stress right
now. and I'm taking it out on you.

490
00:25:00.632 --> 00:25:03.566
Glenn. you got to jiggle the handle.
Oh. Oh!

491
00:25:03.568 --> 00:25:06.536
Oh. did you suddenly
want to talk in private now?

492
00:25:06.538 --> 00:25:08.504
Emma. come on.
You can't leave.

493
00:25:08.506 --> 00:25:11.007
How many times are we gonna
have this conversation?

494
00:25:11.009 --> 00:25:13.176
No. right now. You can't leave right now.
(SIRENS WAILING)

495
00:25:13.178 --> 00:25:15.611
This is the last time we're all gonna be
together like this. (SIRENS BLARING)

496
00:25:15.613 --> 00:25:18.081
The last of our famous couples brunches.

497
00:25:18.083 --> 00:25:20.483
Have you ever. in the last eight years...

498
00:25:20.485 --> 00:25:22.585
No. You know what? Let's go
farther back when we were dating.

499
00:25:22.587 --> 00:25:26.589
So let's say 12 years. Have you
ever in the last 12 years...

500
00:25:26.591 --> 00:25:30.126
Truly looked forward to one
of these couples brunches?

501
00:25:30.128 --> 00:25:31.627
(SIRENS WAILING. BLARING)

502
00:25:31.629 --> 00:25:33.763
Well. what do you mean "looked forward to"?

503
00:25:33.765 --> 00:25:36.666
Look. Emma. you didn't even pack any socks.

504
00:25:36.668 --> 00:25:39.535
Well. I'll buy more.
Where are you gonna go?

505
00:25:39.537 --> 00:25:41.204
It doesn't matter.

506
00:25:41.206 --> 00:25:43.639
Maybe. uh... no. she's not
supposed... that's not the point.

507
00:25:43.641 --> 00:25:45.608
The point is that she...
or toothpaste.

508
00:25:45.610 --> 00:25:48.077
I'll get them at the same store
where socks are sold. Emmers. wait!

509
00:25:48.079 --> 00:25:49.712
Don't call me that!

510
00:25:49.714 --> 00:25:54.083
Um. enjoy my quiche.
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

511
00:25:54.085 --> 00:25:55.752
(SCREAMS)

512
00:25:58.022 --> 00:25:59.522
What?

513
00:25:59.524 --> 00:26:03.026
Um. there's a...
there's a man...

514
00:26:03.028 --> 00:26:05.762
- A man?
- He's wearing a hazmat suit.

515
00:26:05.764 --> 00:26:07.463
(KNOCKING)

516
00:26:10.234 --> 00:26:11.401
It's Hal.

517
00:26:11.403 --> 00:26:13.302
- What?
SHANE: - Who's Hal?

518
00:26:13.304 --> 00:26:15.538
- He's our neighbor.
- Does he always wear a hazmat suit?

519
00:26:15.540 --> 00:26:17.240
What does Hal want?
EMMA: I don't know.

520
00:26:17.242 --> 00:26:19.575
Is there a reason to be afraid of hal?
No. he's nice.

521
00:26:19.577 --> 00:26:22.045
I mean. he doesn't mow his
lawn enough. but I don't...

522
00:26:22.047 --> 00:26:23.579
Can I suggest that maybe we let him in...

523
00:26:23.581 --> 00:26:25.615
And then we can find out
what he wants. from his mouth.

524
00:26:25.617 --> 00:26:27.250
(KNOCKING)

525
00:26:30.621 --> 00:26:31.554
(DOOR CLOSES)

526
00:26:35.192 --> 00:26:37.260
Pete.

527
00:26:37.262 --> 00:26:38.394
Hey. hal.

528
00:26:38.396 --> 00:26:40.329
Emma.

529
00:26:40.331 --> 00:26:41.431
Hey. hal.

530
00:26:43.333 --> 00:26:45.301
You guys having a party?

531
00:26:45.303 --> 00:26:47.637
Just brunch.

532
00:26:47.639 --> 00:26:50.440
Oh. that's cool.

533
00:26:50.442 --> 00:26:52.075
I guess I missed my invite.

534
00:26:52.077 --> 00:26:54.644
It's a couples thing.

535
00:26:54.646 --> 00:26:58.281
Oh. Oh. okay. So I invite you
guys to all my game nights.

536
00:26:58.283 --> 00:27:01.384
My barbecues. but since linda left me. I
guess I don't even socialize anymore.

537
00:27:01.386 --> 00:27:04.087
No. hal. we didn't... no. we
never intended to... I mean...

538
00:27:04.089 --> 00:27:06.789
Hal. Hal. why are you
wearing a hazmat suit?

539
00:27:08.092 --> 00:27:09.725
Are you kidding?

540
00:27:09.727 --> 00:27:11.727
You really don't know
you're wearing a hazmat suit?

541
00:27:12.830 --> 00:27:15.731
- You guys haven't heard?
- Heard what?

542
00:27:15.733 --> 00:27:18.835
That a bunch of dirty bombs
were set off downtown.

543
00:27:21.638 --> 00:27:25.108
Uh. what's a dirty bomb. bro?

544
00:27:25.110 --> 00:27:27.110
It's a radiological weapon.

545
00:27:27.112 --> 00:27:31.581
It combines radioactive material
and conventional explosives.

546
00:27:31.583 --> 00:27:34.250
I'm sorry. Is this like...
are you joking?

547
00:27:34.252 --> 00:27:37.353
No. I was watching the U.T.
Game. and the news cut in.

548
00:27:37.355 --> 00:27:41.224
You guys didn't notice that the power and the
cell phones and land lines all went out?

549
00:27:41.226 --> 00:27:44.360
You just thought you forgot to pay your bill?

550
00:27:44.362 --> 00:27:46.863
Wait. So how many bombs?
What was the blast radius?

551
00:27:46.865 --> 00:27:48.865
Five or six.
It was right downtown.

552
00:27:48.867 --> 00:27:50.433
Oh. my god. It took out half
the financial district.

553
00:27:50.435 --> 00:27:53.669
- Most of Messenier Park.
- Oh. I love that park.

554
00:27:53.671 --> 00:27:55.905
God. I hope the taffy guy is okay.

555
00:27:55.907 --> 00:27:59.175
That's like...
that's like 12 miles away.

556
00:27:59.177 --> 00:28:01.210
If five or six... yeah. Then
the national news cut in.

557
00:28:01.212 --> 00:28:04.647
They said there were attacks on
los angeles. new york. orlando.

558
00:28:04.649 --> 00:28:06.816
And they were about to
say more. but the tv cut out.

559
00:28:06.818 --> 00:28:11.187
Orlando? Someone thinks orlando is on
par with new york and los angeles?

560
00:28:11.189 --> 00:28:12.555
Did they say who did set them off?

561
00:28:13.857 --> 00:28:16.626
Were there any ships or...

562
00:28:16.628 --> 00:28:19.862
- Ships?
- You know. were the attackers not of this earth?

563
00:28:21.765 --> 00:28:23.900
Anyway. the radiation cloud is probably coming.

564
00:28:23.902 --> 00:28:26.669
So I would recommend that you guys
probably tape up your windows.

565
00:28:26.671 --> 00:28:28.804
Close the air vents. put on your hazmat suits.

566
00:28:28.806 --> 00:28:31.240
Who the fuck has a hazmat suit?
Yeah.

567
00:28:31.242 --> 00:28:33.543
I have a hazmat suit.

568
00:28:33.545 --> 00:28:36.679
Hal. if we're supposed to stay inside.
then what are you doing here?

569
00:28:36.681 --> 00:28:41.617
Batteries in my emergency flashlight died.
so I was gonna see if you had any extras.

570
00:28:41.619 --> 00:28:43.019
What kind of batteries?
(CHUCKLES)

571
00:28:45.522 --> 00:28:47.790
I don't... what do you even
use "d" batteries for?

572
00:28:47.792 --> 00:28:49.825
Emergency flashlights.

573
00:28:52.663 --> 00:28:54.330
Do you want to check?

574
00:28:54.332 --> 00:28:55.798
We don't have any.
Yeah. No.

575
00:28:57.334 --> 00:28:59.869
Okay. Well. you guys enjoy
your couples-only brunch.

576
00:28:59.871 --> 00:29:03.673
Yeah. wait. wait. wait. You can't
just leave us here like this.

577
00:29:04.908 --> 00:29:06.609
Yeah. I can.

578
00:29:09.313 --> 00:29:12.215
So that just happened.
(CHUCKLES)

579
00:29:12.217 --> 00:29:15.618
Whoa! That was awesome!
Who is that dude?

580
00:29:15.620 --> 00:29:17.253
It's finally going down.

581
00:29:17.255 --> 00:29:19.822
It's going to be fine.
I just need my adderall.

582
00:29:21.658 --> 00:29:24.527
Well. I guess I'm not going anywhere.

583
00:29:24.529 --> 00:29:28.898
Okay. Uh. all right. Uh. we
heard what he said. Right?

584
00:29:28.900 --> 00:29:32.435
- We need to secure the house.
- Okay. you don't actually believe that guy. do you?

585
00:29:32.437 --> 00:29:35.571
He's probably just huffing some
paint fumes in his garage...

586
00:29:35.573 --> 00:29:37.240
And making this up to screw with us.

587
00:29:37.242 --> 00:29:39.542
No. it makes sense.
It's invasion 101.

588
00:29:39.544 --> 00:29:42.578
You cut off all lines of communication
to keep the locals confused.

589
00:29:42.580 --> 00:29:46.582
Radio! If this is for real.
it'll be all over the radio.

590
00:29:46.584 --> 00:29:48.818
What about the one my mom got us for christmas?

591
00:29:48.820 --> 00:29:52.355
- No. I sold that at a garage sale.
- What? Why?

592
00:29:52.357 --> 00:29:54.924
Because we already have a clock by the
bed. and that one was really ugly.

593
00:29:54.926 --> 00:29:57.994
- When did we have a garage sale? -I had one
when you were in singapore for your convention.

594
00:29:57.996 --> 00:30:01.430
- You had a garage sale when I was out of town?
- I did! You keep everything!

595
00:30:01.432 --> 00:30:03.466
Another radio? Guys. do
you have another radio?

596
00:30:03.468 --> 00:30:05.001
Is there another radio besides that one?

597
00:30:05.003 --> 00:30:08.604
How about some of us look for a radio...

598
00:30:08.606 --> 00:30:11.307
And the rest of us gather supplies
so we can seal up the house?

599
00:30:13.477 --> 00:30:17.313
And if some of us just want to
chill. that's... that's cool too.

600
00:30:18.382 --> 00:30:20.283
Break!

601
00:30:20.285 --> 00:30:21.817
(SIGHS)
I'll keep an eye on the window.

602
00:30:21.819 --> 00:30:23.419
All right.

603
00:30:23.421 --> 00:30:25.588
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

604
00:30:28.492 --> 00:30:32.061
When was the last time we cleaned this?
This is ridiculous.

605
00:30:32.063 --> 00:30:36.465
Oh. my god.
"d" batteries. Oops.

606
00:30:36.467 --> 00:30:38.668
You guys have enough rat poison
down here to kill Chuck E. Cheese.

607
00:30:38.670 --> 00:30:41.737
What is the deal?
Costco is the deal.

608
00:30:45.976 --> 00:30:47.710
Ohh! No.
No?

609
00:30:48.979 --> 00:30:51.447
Oh. sweet!
You found a radio!

610
00:30:51.449 --> 00:30:53.015
(GRUNTS) Check it out.

611
00:30:53.017 --> 00:30:54.650
(SIGHS)

612
00:30:59.856 --> 00:31:01.724
(SIGHS)

613
00:31:09.399 --> 00:31:11.634
I don't think that's gonna help
out in our current situation.

614
00:31:11.636 --> 00:31:14.036
Can we just focus on the task at hand?

615
00:31:14.038 --> 00:31:18.341
What if a bunch of marauders come and
we need to whack them with something?

616
00:31:18.343 --> 00:31:19.842
(CRASH)

617
00:31:27.351 --> 00:31:28.751
Hedy?

618
00:31:29.586 --> 00:31:31.354
Hedy?

619
00:31:34.524 --> 00:31:37.493
- God! There's so much spackling tape!
- Hey. Hey.

620
00:31:37.495 --> 00:31:38.794
It's gonna be all right.

621
00:31:39.930 --> 00:31:41.897
Hey. why didn't you tell me?

622
00:31:41.899 --> 00:31:44.066
About what?
About the divorce.

623
00:31:44.068 --> 00:31:46.669
Is this really the time to be
having his conversation?

624
00:31:51.608 --> 00:31:53.843
Hedy!

625
00:31:53.845 --> 00:31:55.378
Oh.

626
00:31:57.381 --> 00:32:00.716
- How long have you known?
- I don't know. A couple of months.

627
00:32:00.718 --> 00:32:03.652
A couple of months? Yeah. Well.
divorce is complicated...

628
00:32:03.654 --> 00:32:05.488
And it takes a lot of research.

629
00:32:05.490 --> 00:32:07.957
You have to be legally separated. You
have to fill out all these forms.

630
00:32:07.959 --> 00:32:10.626
There's just... there's a lot
of bureaucratic bullshit.

631
00:32:10.628 --> 00:32:13.963
- So then you knew when we had our...
- Yes. of course I did.

632
00:32:13.965 --> 00:32:15.698
Nah. That's cool.

633
00:32:16.867 --> 00:32:19.168
Holy crap.
Are you disappointed?

634
00:32:20.570 --> 00:32:23.806
- You're disappointed.
- Eh.

635
00:32:23.808 --> 00:32:26.008
What? You get. like. more
philandering points or something...

636
00:32:26.010 --> 00:32:27.877
If the woman's happily married?
It's not that.

637
00:32:27.879 --> 00:32:29.979
It's just less of a challenge.

638
00:32:29.981 --> 00:32:32.014
It's like when you're bowling and
they put the things in the gutter.

639
00:32:32.016 --> 00:32:33.115
You're unbelievable.

640
00:32:38.789 --> 00:32:40.423
Shane.

641
00:32:40.425 --> 00:32:43.058
- Hey.
- I think you need to go and help Hedy out.

642
00:32:43.060 --> 00:32:45.060
With what?
She's in shock.

643
00:32:45.062 --> 00:32:46.629
We're all in shock. tracy.
No. no. no.

644
00:32:46.631 --> 00:32:49.632
Like <i>shock</i> shock.
Like real shock.

645
00:32:49.634 --> 00:32:53.002
Okay. I'll be there
in a minute.

646
00:32:53.004 --> 00:32:55.471
Look. we need to talk.
Wait. What? Why?

647
00:32:58.074 --> 00:33:01.010
I don't know if your apathetic attitude
is some sort of coping mechanism...

648
00:33:01.012 --> 00:33:03.179
Due to the stress at hand. which is fine.

649
00:33:03.181 --> 00:33:04.914
Dude. no stress.
None of this shit is real.

650
00:33:04.916 --> 00:33:08.451
Is anyone infected?
Infected with what?

651
00:33:08.453 --> 00:33:10.619
With whatever's out there.

652
00:33:10.621 --> 00:33:12.154
But we don't know what's out there.

653
00:33:12.156 --> 00:33:13.989
And that's exactly what's scaring me.

654
00:33:13.991 --> 00:33:16.125
I mean. how many times
have you seen on the news...

655
00:33:16.127 --> 00:33:20.796
That someone thought. like. a
weather balloon was a U.F.O....

656
00:33:20.798 --> 00:33:23.165
Or a bear was a giant sasquatch?

657
00:33:23.167 --> 00:33:26.235
Just because the media reports
something... (CAN RATTLING)

658
00:33:26.237 --> 00:33:28.037
Doesn't make it true.

659
00:33:28.039 --> 00:33:30.573
Don't even get me started
on the supposed "moon landing."

660
00:33:32.175 --> 00:33:35.110
Have you seen any bite marks. scrapes?

661
00:33:36.546 --> 00:33:38.481
No?
Uh...

662
00:33:38.483 --> 00:33:41.617
All right. well. just... if you see
anyone acting weird. you let me know.

663
00:33:41.619 --> 00:33:44.887
Weirder than you're acting right now?

664
00:33:44.889 --> 00:33:47.089
We might have to make some tough decisions.

665
00:33:49.059 --> 00:33:52.628
Okay. I'm gonna go
check on Hedy.

666
00:33:53.864 --> 00:33:55.798
Thanks. I appreciate that.

667
00:33:57.834 --> 00:34:00.069
God! I don't even know
what we're looking for!

668
00:34:00.071 --> 00:34:03.072
Duck tape.
<i>Duct</i> tape.

669
00:34:03.074 --> 00:34:05.107
That's what I said.

670
00:34:05.109 --> 00:34:07.843
Oh. yeah?
Say it again.

671
00:34:08.678 --> 00:34:09.812
Duck tape.

672
00:34:09.814 --> 00:34:11.614
Duct.

673
00:34:11.616 --> 00:34:13.816
Duct tape.
With a "t."

674
00:34:13.818 --> 00:34:16.919
It's for sealing ducts.

675
00:34:21.791 --> 00:34:23.759
You just blew my mind.

676
00:34:25.795 --> 00:34:28.931
Maybe you're right. Maybe this is a hoax.
I hope it's a hoax.

677
00:34:28.933 --> 00:34:34.069
But the wise thing to do is let's get a
radio. find out for sure. All right?

678
00:34:34.071 --> 00:34:36.171
Whatever floats your boat.
Well. that floats my boat.

679
00:34:36.173 --> 00:34:40.543
Okay. Well. I can't remember the last
time I bought a radio. except for my car.

680
00:34:41.678 --> 00:34:43.178
Ohh.

681
00:34:48.618 --> 00:34:50.886
Hey. uh. where are your car keys?

682
00:34:50.888 --> 00:34:53.022
Huh?
Your keys.

683
00:34:53.024 --> 00:34:55.991
- Where you goin'. glenn?
- Nowhere. I just need your keys.

684
00:34:55.993 --> 00:34:58.227
They're sit...
flamingo key chain.

685
00:34:59.930 --> 00:35:01.797
Well. there's...
