(TOGETHER) <i>♪ Mothers</i>

1411
01:10:41.837 --> 01:10:43.036
<i>♪ Tell your children...</i>

1412
01:10:43.038 --> 01:10:44.271
No!

1413
01:10:44.273 --> 01:10:46.006
- What the fuck?
- What gives?

1414
01:10:46.008 --> 01:10:49.109
(OTHERS SHOUTING)
- Shut up!

1415
01:10:49.111 --> 01:10:51.411
Now. if you guys wanna sing "kumbaya"
as the world's about to end.

1416
01:10:51.413 --> 01:10:53.747
Then by my guest.

1417
01:10:53.749 --> 01:10:56.717
But I'm not gonna just sit in
here and lay down like a dog.

1418
01:11:00.955 --> 01:11:02.923
Now. the way I see it.

1419
01:11:02.925 --> 01:11:05.025
We've an hour. maybe two.

1420
01:11:05.027 --> 01:11:06.960
Before the air runs out.

1421
01:11:06.962 --> 01:11:09.096
So if we're gonna make a move.
it's gotta be right now.

1422
01:11:09.098 --> 01:11:11.498
Yeah. but what move is that?

1423
01:11:11.500 --> 01:11:13.133
I'm taking the S.U.V..
and I'm getting outta here.

1424
01:11:13.135 --> 01:11:15.268
Where are you gonna go?

1425
01:11:15.270 --> 01:11:17.304
I don't know.

1426
01:11:17.306 --> 01:11:18.505
Is that my backpack?
Yeah.

1427
01:11:18.507 --> 01:11:20.340
If I roll up the windows.
kill the a.C..

1428
01:11:20.342 --> 01:11:22.409
It'll give me some time.

1429
01:11:22.411 --> 01:11:25.245
Not long. but...

1430
01:11:25.247 --> 01:11:27.481
Maybe enough time to find something. anything.

1431
01:11:29.484 --> 01:11:32.185
And it might be a fool's errand.

1432
01:11:32.187 --> 01:11:33.820
But I'm not gonna regret it.

1433
01:11:33.822 --> 01:11:36.423
'cause I know that if I die.

1434
01:11:36.425 --> 01:11:38.992
At least I died trying.

1435
01:11:41.229 --> 01:11:43.196
Who's with me?

1436
01:11:43.198 --> 01:11:45.132
(DOOR SLAMS)
(MURMURING. CLEARING THROATS)

1437
01:11:45.134 --> 01:11:49.269
Okay. everybody take calm.
short breaths to conserve air.

1438
01:11:49.271 --> 01:11:51.872
And keep the talking to a minimum.
Right.

1439
01:11:51.874 --> 01:11:53.907
Starting now.

1440
01:11:53.909 --> 01:11:55.275
Are we ready?

1441
01:11:56.778 --> 01:11:59.179
Here we go.
(IGNITION CLICKS)

1442
01:12:04.285 --> 01:12:07.854
Say. Glenn. when you checked my radio earlier.

1443
01:12:07.856 --> 01:12:09.489
Did you remember to turn the car off after?

1444
01:12:09.491 --> 01:12:12.893
Lexi... Lexi was in here
listening to music.

1445
01:12:12.895 --> 01:12:15.428
Lexi.
Lexi was listening...

1446
01:12:15.430 --> 01:12:17.497
We were in here too.
Oh. my gosh.

1447
01:12:17.499 --> 01:12:21.067
(♪ CLASSICAL. MELANCHOLY)

1448
01:12:21.069 --> 01:12:25.438
(♪ GLOCKENSPIEL: SINGLE NOTE REPEATING)

1449
01:12:41.189 --> 01:12:44.858
I know I'm new to the group. but...

1450
01:12:44.860 --> 01:12:49.362
I think we should set the table and...

1451
01:12:49.364 --> 01:12:52.432
Eat like we were supposed to.

1452
01:12:52.434 --> 01:12:55.035
You know. I think we should eat and drink...

1453
01:12:55.037 --> 01:12:57.838
And swap stories.

1454
01:12:57.840 --> 01:13:00.373
You know. and... and...
and enjoy couples brunch...

1455
01:13:03.377 --> 01:13:05.145
The way we were meant to.

1456
01:13:07.915 --> 01:13:10.250
I can be down for that.

1457
01:13:10.252 --> 01:13:12.519
It would be a shame to see
my quiche go to waste.

1458
01:13:12.521 --> 01:13:15.956
Yeah. Well.
then let's do it.

1459
01:13:15.958 --> 01:13:17.457
Is your quiche vegan? Yes.

1460
01:13:19.093 --> 01:13:21.461
How about you. shane?
You hungry?

1461
01:13:21.463 --> 01:13:24.564
Nah. I'm good.
HEDY: Come on. Shane.

1462
01:13:24.566 --> 01:13:27.067
When the north koreans come...

1463
01:13:27.069 --> 01:13:30.503
And they take you away to some makeshift camp.

1464
01:13:30.505 --> 01:13:33.039
They're probably not gonna feed
you anything more than gruel...

1465
01:13:33.041 --> 01:13:35.075
For. like. days.

1466
01:13:35.077 --> 01:13:37.277
North korean food does suck.

1467
01:13:37.279 --> 01:13:40.013
Okay. okay.
Well. great.

1468
01:13:40.015 --> 01:13:41.514
Right?
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

1469
01:13:41.516 --> 01:13:44.251
Okay. good.
Let's... let's do this.

1470
01:13:44.253 --> 01:13:47.454
I'm gonna go grab
some wine. Yeah?

1471
01:13:49.357 --> 01:13:50.924
Okay.

1472
01:13:50.926 --> 01:13:54.628
(WIND WHISTLING)

1473
01:13:54.630 --> 01:13:56.196
(♪ PIANO. CLASSICAL)
EMMA: <i>Okay. I got one.</i>

1474
01:13:56.198 --> 01:13:58.265
Uh. something I've never told anyone.

1475
01:13:58.267 --> 01:14:00.667
When I used to work at that
pizza place in college.

1476
01:14:00.669 --> 01:14:03.637
Um. I used to take money from the register.

1477
01:14:03.639 --> 01:14:06.673
Wow. Really?
Mm-hmm. yep.

1478
01:14:06.675 --> 01:14:09.042
Why? So I could steal it. Pete.

1479
01:14:09.044 --> 01:14:12.145
Why do you think? All right.
Yeah. granted. but...

1480
01:14:12.147 --> 01:14:15.115
How much... how much did you take?
Uh. you know.

1481
01:14:15.117 --> 01:14:17.984
Probably just. like. three grand.

1482
01:14:17.986 --> 01:14:20.587
(ALL EXCLAIMING)
Just. like. three grand?

1483
01:14:20.589 --> 01:14:23.290
And I'm... I'm impressed. That's... wow.
Thank you.

1484
01:14:23.292 --> 01:14:24.991
BUCK:
Okay. I've got one.

1485
01:14:24.993 --> 01:14:27.928
This is something I've never told anyone.

1486
01:14:30.464 --> 01:14:32.565
I fucking love <i>love actually.</i>

1487
01:14:32.567 --> 01:14:35.335
There's nothing wrong with that. I'm serious.
I watch it every christmas.

1488
01:14:35.337 --> 01:14:37.170
Why are you ashamed of that?
I love that movie.

1489
01:14:37.172 --> 01:14:38.672
I'm not anymore.
I'm free now.

1490
01:14:38.674 --> 01:14:40.573
You worked through it.
I'm proud of you.

1491
01:14:40.575 --> 01:14:42.575
- I think I killed somebody.
(CHATTERING STOPS)

1492
01:14:44.078 --> 01:14:46.146
This one night. I was driving home.

1493
01:14:46.148 --> 01:14:49.149
And this homeless guy just stepped
right out in front of me.

1494
01:14:49.151 --> 01:14:50.717
Bam.

1495
01:14:52.153 --> 01:14:54.187
And I just took off.

1496
01:14:57.591 --> 01:15:02.529
Well. Pete. I'm sure there was
nothing you could've done.

1497
01:15:02.531 --> 01:15:05.065
Oh. no. there was.

1498
01:15:05.067 --> 01:15:06.533
He was still breathing when I left.

1499
01:15:09.070 --> 01:15:11.137
(FOOTSTEPS DESCENDING STAIRS)
TRACY: Glenn?

1500
01:15:11.139 --> 01:15:14.307
I'll be up in a minute.

1501
01:15:14.309 --> 01:15:16.229
Glenn. what are you doing down here?
Everybody...

1502
01:15:25.052 --> 01:15:27.153
Tracy. are you familiar with the rapture?

1503
01:15:27.755 --> 01:15:30.256
The band...

1504
01:15:30.258 --> 01:15:32.058
Or the blondie song?

1505
01:15:33.728 --> 01:15:36.496
The prophecies in the book of revelations.

1506
01:15:36.498 --> 01:15:38.765
No. I don't like where this is going.

1507
01:15:38.767 --> 01:15:41.201
At the end of times. all true believers...

1508
01:15:41.203 --> 01:15:43.069
Who are alive before armageddon...

1509
01:15:43.071 --> 01:15:45.071
Which is the final battle of the apocalypse.

1510
01:15:45.073 --> 01:15:48.074
Which... Had clearly started...

1511
01:15:48.076 --> 01:15:52.545
Will be taken by god from earth to heaven.

1512
01:15:53.514 --> 01:15:56.483
All the nonbelievers...

1513
01:15:56.485 --> 01:16:00.186
Will be forced to walk a hell on earth...

1514
01:16:00.188 --> 01:16:02.489
For a seven-year period
of tribulations...

1515
01:16:02.491 --> 01:16:04.657
In which they will sit in judgment.

1516
01:16:04.659 --> 01:16:07.660
I fear for all of you.

1517
01:16:07.662 --> 01:16:11.765
I love you. tracy. and I love your friends.

1518
01:16:11.767 --> 01:16:14.234
I have huge love for them.

1519
01:16:15.636 --> 01:16:17.404
And I want to help with their judgment.

1520
01:16:18.372 --> 01:16:20.673
Tracy. I...

1521
01:16:22.043 --> 01:16:25.045
Would like to ask you...

1522
01:16:25.047 --> 01:16:28.381
To sit beside me at the
marriage supper of the lamb.

1523
01:16:28.383 --> 01:16:30.216
(WHIMPERS)

1524
01:16:31.185 --> 01:16:34.220
(QUAVERING VOICE) Oh. man.

1525
01:16:36.657 --> 01:16:37.791
Well...

1526
01:16:42.530 --> 01:16:44.531
(SIGHS)

1527
01:16:44.533 --> 01:16:46.499
Honey?
Oh. whoa!

1528
01:16:47.435 --> 01:16:48.735
Yeah.

1529
01:16:50.538 --> 01:16:52.172
EMMA: Honey? Yeah.

1530
01:16:52.174 --> 01:16:54.407
He's crazy.
Who's crazy?

1531
01:16:54.409 --> 01:16:56.443
He's crazy.
Glenn.

1532
01:16:56.445 --> 01:16:58.478
I think he's really cool.
I do. Yeah.

1533
01:16:58.480 --> 01:17:00.380
- I think...
- No. No. no. no.

1534
01:17:00.382 --> 01:17:02.849
He's certifiable. He belongs in
a tiny little padded room...

1535
01:17:02.851 --> 01:17:04.684
With one tiny little window.

1536
01:17:04.686 --> 01:17:06.352
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1537
01:17:07.588 --> 01:17:09.489
(CHUCKLING) Hey.

1538
01:17:09.491 --> 01:17:12.051
PETE: - I found some wine. Perfect timing.
EMMA: - Great.

1539
01:17:14.528 --> 01:17:16.596
And I'm sure. tracy.

1540
01:17:16.598 --> 01:17:19.632
That you are probably just...

1541
01:17:19.634 --> 01:17:21.835
Taking one thing about that person...

1542
01:17:21.837 --> 01:17:23.803
And blowing it out of proportion.

1543
01:17:23.805 --> 01:17:26.439
No. No. No. I'm not.
I'm not.

1544
01:17:26.441 --> 01:17:29.509
You always think that I am.
but I never am. I never am.

1545
01:17:29.511 --> 01:17:33.146
I know you think that I'm some sad.
pathetic character from a cathy cartoon...

1546
01:17:33.148 --> 01:17:35.381
Or a sitcom that brooke
shields would've been in.

1547
01:17:35.383 --> 01:17:39.219
But it's true.
It's always true.

1548
01:17:39.221 --> 01:17:40.320
He poisoned your wine. by the way.

1549
01:17:40.322 --> 01:17:41.855
(GAGS)
- What? He did what?

1550
01:17:43.824 --> 01:17:46.259
Guilty as charged.

1551
01:17:46.261 --> 01:17:48.161
What the fuck? Glenn. you're
a guest in this house.

1552
01:17:48.163 --> 01:17:50.530
- That is not fucking cool. dude.
- No!

1553
01:17:50.532 --> 01:17:52.866
- Okay. Everybody calm down.
- You calm down!

1554
01:17:52.868 --> 01:17:57.403
I am calm. shane.
I'm extremely calm.

1555
01:17:57.405 --> 01:17:59.405
- We can see that. Glenn.
- What's in this?

1556
01:17:59.407 --> 01:18:01.908
Well. I crushed up about 40 sleeping pills...

1557
01:18:01.910 --> 01:18:04.444
And. uh. 30 muscle relaxants.

1558
01:18:04.446 --> 01:18:08.481
And then I put in a... a good
heaping amount of rat poison.

1559
01:18:08.483 --> 01:18:11.217
Are you trying to kill us?

1560
01:18:11.219 --> 01:18:13.686
Yes. Hedy. I'm trying to kill you.

1561
01:18:13.688 --> 01:18:17.390
Oh. well. then that would do the trick.

1562
01:18:17.392 --> 01:18:22.295
That jesus christ... sorry...
is gonna put us all on trial?

1563
01:18:22.297 --> 01:18:24.497
You're paraphrasing.
She's paraphrasing.

1564
01:18:24.499 --> 01:18:27.333
Oh. okay. My bad. My bad.
Let me rephrase that.

1565
01:18:27.335 --> 01:18:30.870
Johnny crazy balls over here is gonna
save us all from seeing armageddon.

1566
01:18:30.872 --> 01:18:33.706
That movie was awesome. So that
is what is going to happen?

1567
01:18:33.708 --> 01:18:35.842
Okay. let <i>me rephrase that.
Please.</i>

1568
01:18:37.878 --> 01:18:39.579
This is very serious.

1569
01:18:39.581 --> 01:18:42.749
Every one of you sitting at this table...

1570
01:18:42.751 --> 01:18:46.486
Will sit before st. Peter
as he judges you...

1571
01:18:46.488 --> 01:18:48.721
To see whether you gain entrance into heaven.

1572
01:18:48.723 --> 01:18:52.458
Now. <i>I</i> am going to heaven.
That is a fact.

1573
01:18:52.460 --> 01:18:57.463
I desperately want you all to join me there.

1574
01:18:57.465 --> 01:19:00.533
If you drink this wine. you
stand a far greater chance...

1575
01:19:00.535 --> 01:19:03.570
Of spending the rest of eternity in heaven.

1576
01:19:06.273 --> 01:19:08.675
- Wow. You were right.
- You see?

1577
01:19:08.677 --> 01:19:10.643
You see? Do you see?

1578
01:19:10.645 --> 01:19:12.645
Is shit in the Bible. or are you making this up?

1579
01:19:12.647 --> 01:19:14.547
"No one knows the days or hours.

1580
01:19:14.549 --> 01:19:16.249
(TOGETHER) not even
the angels in heaven."

1581
01:19:16.251 --> 01:19:18.952
Matthew 24:36.

1582
01:19:18.954 --> 01:19:21.754
Lexi. Yes.

1583
01:19:22.957 --> 01:19:24.824
You see. Buck. I teach this for a living.

1584
01:19:24.826 --> 01:19:26.726
So I know what I'm talking about.

1585
01:19:26.728 --> 01:19:29.729
- I thought you said you teach history.
- Because I do teach history.

1586
01:19:29.731 --> 01:19:32.232
I teach bible history.
That is history.

1587
01:19:32.234 --> 01:19:34.534
You didn't put that in your
internet profile. now. did ya?

1588
01:19:34.536 --> 01:19:36.002
I thought you met at a grocery store.

1589
01:19:36.004 --> 01:19:37.904
I don't wanna be the one to say this.

1590
01:19:37.906 --> 01:19:40.240
But I think Glenn might
actually be onto something.

1591
01:19:40.242 --> 01:19:43.343
What? Have you gone fuckin' insane too?
No offense.

1592
01:19:45.646 --> 01:19:48.982
Purely from a biological standpoint.

1593
01:19:48.984 --> 01:19:50.917
When the nerve gas slips into the house...

1594
01:19:50.919 --> 01:19:53.786
And it will eventually slip into the house...

1595
01:19:53.788 --> 01:19:55.855
We are all going to go through a very long...

1596
01:19:55.857 --> 01:19:59.859
And a very painful ordeal.

1597
01:19:59.861 --> 01:20:02.028
Ordeal? What do you mean "ordeal"?
Yeah.

1598
01:20:02.030 --> 01:20:03.997
That sounds ominous.
I don't like ominous.

1599
01:20:03.999 --> 01:20:06.432
Deets. please.
EMMA: Yeah.

1600
01:20:07.401 --> 01:20:10.503
Okay. Uh. well.

1601
01:20:10.505 --> 01:20:13.740
You might start with blurred
vision and a headache.

1602
01:20:15.476 --> 01:20:18.511
Move quickly to nausea.

1603
01:20:18.513 --> 01:20:21.614
Intense vomiting and diarrhea.

1604
01:20:21.616 --> 01:20:23.950
That would be followed by copious sweating.

1605
01:20:23.952 --> 01:20:26.519
Involuntary muscle twitching.

1606
01:20:26.521 --> 01:20:28.588
(WOMAN SINGING <i>"AVE MARIA"</i>)
Then there's the blindness.

1607
01:20:28.590 --> 01:20:31.057
Dyspnea and seizures.

1608
01:20:33.427 --> 01:20:36.696
The initial violent contractions...

1609
01:20:36.698 --> 01:20:39.766
Will turn into sustained
super-contractions.

1610
01:20:39.768 --> 01:20:43.369
Which results in the paralysis
of all the muscles in your body.

1611
01:20:43.371 --> 01:20:46.839
And ultimately it's the paralysis
of the diaphragm muscle...

1612
01:20:46.841 --> 01:20:49.876
That leads to death by asphyxiation.

1613
01:20:51.879 --> 01:20:55.982
If we're lucky. we could lose
consciousness before some of that.

1614
01:20:55.984 --> 01:20:57.917
If we're lucky.

1615
01:20:59.921 --> 01:21:01.587
So.

1616
01:21:02.556 --> 01:21:03.890
Well. I'm in.

1617
01:21:03.892 --> 01:21:05.692
Till death do us part.
Mm-hmm.

1618
01:21:05.694 --> 01:21:09.629
Seriously? We're just gonna
go all jonestown on this?

1619
01:21:09.631 --> 01:21:12.398
Did you not just hear that laundry
list she just rattled off?

1620
01:21:12.400 --> 01:21:15.868
I don't even know what a "disnepsis"
is. but I don't fuckin' want it.

1621
01:21:15.870 --> 01:21:17.937
It's gonna be a lot less
painful to drink the wine.

1622
01:21:17.939 --> 01:21:19.772
Yes.

1623
01:21:19.774 --> 01:21:23.643
Well. it... it might be better
than me falling into enemy hands.

1624
01:21:23.645 --> 01:21:26.612
Given my knowledge of american pop culture...

1625
01:21:26.614 --> 01:21:30.049
And the industrial-military
complex. but...

1626
01:21:30.051 --> 01:21:31.551
Do you have any white?

1627
01:21:31.553 --> 01:21:33.453
I'm sorry?

1628
01:21:34.655 --> 01:21:36.589
If this is gonna be my last drink on earth.

1629
01:21:36.591 --> 01:21:39.359
I just don't really care for merlot.

1630
01:21:39.361 --> 01:21:40.993
GLENN:
Can... can I jump in?

1631
01:21:40.995 --> 01:21:43.062
When I was down there. and I...

1632
01:21:43.064 --> 01:21:45.098
I had some of the wine before
I put all the stuff in it.

1633
01:21:45.100 --> 01:21:47.567
And. um. it's pretty good merlot.

1634
01:21:47.569 --> 01:21:49.769
- It really is.
- I'm sure it is. but still...

1635
01:21:49.771 --> 01:21:51.671
Shane. will you just drink the fucking red wine?

1636
01:21:53.807 --> 01:21:56.743
Wait. wait. wait. wait.
I mean...

1637
01:21:56.745 --> 01:21:58.411
It kind of makes sense. but...

1638
01:21:58.413 --> 01:22:00.079
Can we all agree that I'm right.
that he's fucking crazy?

1639
01:22:00.081 --> 01:22:02.415
(ALL AGREEING. MURMURING)

1640
01:22:02.417 --> 01:22:04.517
GLENN: Well. can I
tell you someone else...

1641
01:22:04.519 --> 01:22:06.452
Who was considered
the f-word crazy?

1642
01:22:06.454 --> 01:22:08.955
Was saul of tarsus. so...

1643
01:22:12.559 --> 01:22:14.093
What do you think?

1644
01:22:15.596 --> 01:22:16.996
No.
No?

1645
01:22:16.998 --> 01:22:18.765
No.

1646
01:22:18.767 --> 01:22:20.800
I mean. what...

1647
01:22:20.802 --> 01:22:22.935
What if a swat team comes
bursting through the door...

1648
01:22:22.937 --> 01:22:25.705
At the last minute to save our lives?

